sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K145101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: OmpF PoPS -> deactivate constitutive antisense LuxI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Memory device in which P2ogr is under control of OmpF and Psid double promotor. P2ogr will also activate transcription of cII from a seperate Psid promotor. This cII represses transcription of antisense LuxI from a P22 promotor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Demeulemeester

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompF. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter includes three OmpR binding sites: F1, F2, and F3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1. A distant fourth binding site, F4, has been deleted. It is involved in negative regulation of ompF (Head, Tardy and Kenney, 1998), so its deletion is intended to make the promoter solely activating. The efficacy of this promoter versus the ompC upstream region (BBa_R0082) or the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) is currently unknown.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: c2 P22
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: c2 repressor from Salmonella phage P22 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The P22 c2 repressor protein coding sequence is a 720 base-pair sequence with the standard RBS-compatible BioBrick prefix and the standard BioBrick suffix sections on its ends. It binds to the P22 c2 regulatory sequence, BBa_R0053. The sequence contains a LVA tag for faster degredation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

Vander Byl,C. and Kropinski,A.M. Sequence of the genome of Salmonella bacteriophage P22
J. Bacteriol. 182 (22), 6472-6481 (2000)

References (unparsed) here:

Vander Byl,C. and Kropinski,A.M. Sequence of the genome of Salmonella bacteriophage P22
J. Bacteriol. 182 (22), 6472-6481 (2000)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Maia Mahoney

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746350
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: plasmid DNA supplied by Prof. Richard Calendar, University of California.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The ogr activator taken from P2 phage acts on a class of inducible promoters (parts I746360 to I746365), inducing their activity to varying degrees. The part sequence does already contain a ribosome binding site (B0034)!
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part does contain a RBS (B0034) already.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746364
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the Psid promoter taken from the P4 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the Psid promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cII p22
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The p22 cII regulatory region sequence is a 97 base-pair sequence with the standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. p22 cII repressor protein, BBa_C0053, binds to it.
This segment contains O-R1, O-R2, a fragment of O-R3, the -35 of P-RM, and P-R (-10 and -35 from Tom Knight)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Maia Mahoney

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
